By default, will order the prompt in the metadata in an A1111 style, where the overall prompt comes first, then the individual region prompts are separated by ADDCOL.
By default, the initial KSampler node is set to Euler CFG++. The CFG NEEDS to be in the range 1.0 <= x < 2.0, or it will be oversaturated! Use a non CFG++ sampler if you don't want to deal with this.

Creates a simple 50/50 column split by default. This can be easily setup differently, or an image's mask can be loaded instead. I recommend using the Get Image Size node from the masquerade-nodes-comfyui family to easily set up the width/height based on an image.

This part of the workflow creates the overall prompt, or rather the prompt that persists throughout all regions to deliever a coherent image. All of this goes into the condition input on the Region Attention node.

By default, we will accomplish the following prompt structure: ([artist tags], [gentags], [quality tags]). Feel free to change the inputs of the Text Concatenate node to change this order.

By default, this is set to a simple, two-region setup. It can be very easily extended beyond two regions.

This is not a 100% perfect regional prompt implementation (not that I think one exists), you may have to experiment with different prompts and prompt layouts for the overall prompt and the regional prompts to get the results you want. Consider setting up the region bbox nodes or the mask nodes differently depending on what you want to get, as well as considering what resolutions to use for a particular idea.

If you are looking to get something VERY specific, you may want to consider making an image and grabbing masks from the image to get very specifically defined regions.
